ta. We conclude that our models can reproduce many of the\ncharacteristics of both flux and polarization spectra for well-studied Type Ia\nsupernovae, such as SN 2001el and SN 2012fr. However, the two models considered\nhere cannot account for the unusually high level of polarization observed in\nextreme cases such as SN 2004dt.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2016 10:49:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-15"}
